author: Slidebean
description:
Scammers now have real time face swapping and it already made millions

Ocean wasn’t a research demo, it was a fully commercial product marketed to scammers, enabling real time facial impersonation during video calls.
Its disappearance after media scrutiny doesn’t signal resolution, but maturation.

As fraud tools become subscription software with support teams and onboarding, the line between cybercrime and SaaS continues to blur.
The challenge ahead isn’t detection alone, it’s rebuilding trust in a world where seeing someone’s face is no longer proof of identity.

title: Why real time deepfake tools represent a new phase of online fraud
